oai_dc:dc.dc:title: The AT&T Building in downtown Nashville, Tennessee, 2015 May 22
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: A view of the AT&T Building (333 Commerce Street, Nashville, Tennessee), a postmodern 33-story skyscraper completed in August 1994. It was formerly the South Central Bell Building and BellSouth Building. This office tower is informally known as the "Batman Building," and stands at approx. 617 ft. (188.1 m). Additional buildings in view are the Life & Casualty Tower (also known as the L & C Tower), the Fifth Third Center, and Regions Bank. Forms part of the Leanne Garland Photograph Collection. 1 digital photograph.
